<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14618 AND RTLO-16618
        SERIES - REASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the gear shift lever housing secured in a vise, install the spade pin in the bore
                    of the housing tower (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13019e5">Figure 145</hotlnk>). If previously removed, install the O-ring in the
                    tower groove.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13019e5" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13019e5" filename="../figg13/G13019E5.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 145. Install Spade Pin in Housing Tower Bore</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the gear shift lever in the housing with the spade pin in the lever ball slot
                    and install the tension spring washer over the ball, dished-side up (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13019e6">Figure 146</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13019e6" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13019e6" filename="../figg13/G13019E6.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 146. Install Tension Spring Washer</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the tension spring under the lugs in the housing,
                    <emph type="bold">seating one coil at a time</emph>
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13019e7">Figure 147</hotlnk>). Use of a spring driving tool is recommended.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13019e7" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13019e7" filename="../figg13/G13019E7.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 147. Install Tension Spring Under Lugs</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the assembly from the vise and install the rubber boot over the gear shift lever
                    and against the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13019e8">Figure 148</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13019e8" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13019e8" filename="../figg13/G13019E8.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 148. Install Rubber Boot Over Gear Shift Lever</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
